'''Meditieshan''' a praktis we wah indivijal chrien deh main ar injuus wah muod a kanchosnis, aida fi riilaiz soh benifit ar fi di main fi simpli aknalij ikantent widoutn bikom aidentifai wid daa kantent,<ref>Lutz etal., "Attention regulation and monitoring in meditation," ''Trends in Cognitive Sciences'', Volume 12, Issue 4, pp. 163–9 </ref> ar az a hen ina iself.<ref>Watts, Alan. "11 _10-4-1 Meditation." ''Eastern Wisdom: Zen in the West & Meditations.'' The Alan Watts Foundation. 2009. MP3 CD. @4:45</ref> 

Di toerm ''meditieshan'' refa tu a braad varayati a praktis we ingkluud tekniik dizain fi prumuot rilaxieshan, bil intoernal enaji ar laif fuos (''[[Chii|chii]]'', ''[[Rieki|Rieki]]'', ''[[Praana|praana]]'', etc.) ah divelop kompashan,<ref>University of Wisconsin-Madison (2008, March 27). [http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/03/080326204236.htm/ Compassion Meditation Changes The Brain]. ScienceDaily. Richriiv 1 November 1 2012, frah </ref> lob, pieshans, jinarasiti ah fagivnis. Wah potikiula ambishos faam a meditieshan iem fi efatles sostien singgl-paint kansenchrieshan<ref>Gen. Lamrimpa (author); "Calming the Mind." Snow Lion Publications. 1995. Buk pah Budis metod fi divelop singgl paint kansenchrieshan.</ref> miin fi iniebl di praktishana fi injai indischroktebl sens a wel-biin wails ingiej ina ''h''eni laif aktiviti.

